-- Stefan Wieler Said to Be Leaving Goldman Sachs
-- B y   M a r k   S h e n k
-- 2013-08-02T17:31:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-02/stefan-wieler-said-to-be-leaving-goldman-sachs.html
Stefan Wieler, a Goldman Sachs Group
Inc. commodity analyst in  New York , is leaving the company after
four years, a person familiar with the situation said.  Today is Wieler’s last day at Goldman Sachs, said the
person, who isn’t authorized to speak for the company and asked
not to be identified. Wieler didn’t answer two calls to his
office or respond to an e-mailed request for an interview.  Wieler said in an e-mail from his Goldman Sachs account
that he was leaving after four years at the New York-based
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Shenk in New York at 
 mshenk1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Banker at 
 bbanker@bloomberg.net  